CLIMATE PROTEST: STUDENTS ARE RIGHT TO PROTEST

Secondary students from across the country are leaving schools to join protests across the country today. They have every right to do so – their future is being threatened by hypocritical politicians who talk ‘concern’ but do little.
Ireland has one of the worst records in Europe – as a direct result of policies pursued by Fine Gael and Fianna Fail.
They are:

• Proceeding with an extra runway at Dublin Airport;
• Continuing to pursue international data centres that consume vast quantities of electricity;
• Continuing to subsidise peat production with high Co2 emissions;
• Supporting the construction of Liquefied Natural Gas Terminals at Shannon and
• Cork that will house massive quantities of fracked North American gas;
• Continuing to issue exploration licences to oil and gas companies;
• Blocking People Before Profit’s Bill to keep fossil fuels in the ground;
• Continuing to increase the beef and dairy herds in line with Harvest 2025.

To save our planet we need radical action. We need free public transport to get people out of cars. We need to impose an immediate ban on exploring for fossil fuels. We need a major state led retro-fitting programme to create green jobs by insulating homes.
Saving the climate is about more than choosing a colour. In this election, it has become obvious that the Green Party will join a government led by Fianna Fail.
That will do little to tackle the climate crisis. We need to Break the Cycle of endless FF/FG rule. That means voting NO 1 for People Before Profit.
You can access our detailed Planet Before Profit manifesto here.  https://eco.pbp.ie/

